result.execSummary:
The defendant Julio Cesar Roque-Rojas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant may petition for early termination of probation term after completion of 1 year, provided request is joined by agent and all financial obligations are paid in full and all treatment programming is completed.

miscConds.notes: Court Appointed Attorney's Fees and the Court Costs paid in full with deposits and cash bond previously posted.
Defendant to obtain either a GED or HSED during the pendency of probation term.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Defendant to complete either a Domestic Abuse Alternatives Program or an Anger Management Program as coordinated by the supervising agent, together with any follow through counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent. DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 3:48 PM: Defendant Julio Cesar Roque-Rojas in court with attorney Jeffrey Allen Mann.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Oath administered at previous hearing today.  Agreement on resolution recited by ADA with argued terms on sentencing.  Def and counsel concur w/State's recital.  ADA confirms no request rec'd for Restitution.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct 1 Battery w/Dom Ab Enh:  NC   Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Ct 2 DRI.  Argument by ADA.  Argument by Atty Mann - Argues for a lesser term of supervision.  Statement by Def: None offered.  The Court:  Takes in account the wishes of the victim and responsibility accepted  by Def - S/W - 2 yrs probation.  May petition the court at any time after completion of 1 yr if agent joins in the request for early termination, complete AODA and any follow thru as recommended; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician;  Def must complete an Anger Mgmt or Dom Abuse Violence program as coordinated by supervising agent - due to language barrier the Court is not aware of what exactly would be available to Def; complete either HSED or GED; Court Costs plus DNA surcharge and sample.  Sample to be provided directly to WCJ today.    Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Bond to be applied to Ct Appt Atty Fees first and any balance to be applied to other costs.   Court will not grant request for expungement.  1 day TS credit.    Hispanic Appeal Rights Given.
